level_description_from_recommendations_v: Include at least 1 serving of vegetables at every main meal (breakfast, lunch, dinner), with at least 2 different vegetable sources per day
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Regular vegetable intake supports metabolic health, cardiovascular resilience, and digestive function. Vegetables provide essential micronutrients, fiber, and phytonutrients linked to healthy aging, inflammation reduction, and chronic disease risk reduction.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Reach 5 or more servings of vegetables daily, with at least 3 different vegetable sources per day
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Regular vegetable intake supports metabolic health, cardiovascular resilience, and digestive function. Vegetables provide essential micronutrients, fiber, and phytonutrients linked to healthy aging, inflammation reduction, and chronic disease risk reduction.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Include at least 1 serving of fruit at every main meal (breakfast, lunch, dinner), with at least 2 different fruit sources per day
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Regular fruit intake provides essential vitamins, minerals, antioxidants, and fiber. Eating a variety of fruits supports metabolic health, immune function, healthy aging, and helps lower risk of chronic diseases.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Reach 5 or more servings of fruit daily, with at least 3 different fruit sources per day
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Regular fruit intake provides essential vitamins, minerals, antioxidants, and fiber. Eating a variety of fruits supports metabolic health, immune function, healthy aging, and helps lower risk of chronic diseases.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Reach 3 or more servings of whole grains daily, with at least 2 different whole grain sources across the week
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Whole grains are rich in fiber, vitamins, and minerals that support metabolic, digestive, and cardiovascular health. Regular intake is linked to longevity and reduced risk.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Include 2 servings of legumes daily, with at least 2 different legumes per week
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Legumes provide plant-based protein, fiber, and micronutrients that promote metabolic, digestive, and cardiovascular health. Regular intake supports longevity and gut health.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Reach 3 or more servings of legumes daily, with at least 3 different legume sources across the week
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Legumes provide plant-based protein, fiber, and micronutrients that promote metabolic, digestive, and cardiovascular health. Regular intake supports longevity and gut health.

config_name: Composite Daily - meal frequency plus healthy snack
level_description_from_recommendations_v: Eat 3 or more meals per day every day of the week, with at least 1 healthy snack
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Regular meal frequency supports stable energy, muscle maintenance, metabolic health, and balanced nutrient intake. Eating too few meals can increase fatigue and undernutrition risk.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Complete at least 5 exercise snacks per day, including 2 after meals
overview_from_recommendations_v2: “Exercise snacks”—short bursts of movement—improve metabolic health, mood, and energy, and make movement more achievable in busy schedules.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Complete at least 8 exercise snacks per day, including after every meal
overview_from_recommendations_v2: “Exercise snacks”—short bursts of movement—improve metabolic health, mood, and energy, and make movement more achievable in busy schedules.

level_description_from_recommendations_v: Incorporate 2 or more breathwork sessions and 2 or more mindfulness breaks daily
overview_from_recommendations_v2: Breathwork and mindfulness can lower stress, support emotional health, and improve focus.
